What you need to know:

As a good practice, after harvesting, clear the block and prepare for the planting of the next crop.It is also important to practice crop rotation for maximum utilisation of nutrients and prevent the spread of pest and diseases to the next crop.Some of the lessons we learnt during the production is that pests and diseases infestation is inevitable, but timely interventions are paramount before the pests have fully damaged the crop affecting the production.Farming is like any other business that requires adequate planning and commitment.